title: Integrating Human Proteomes with Genome-Wide Association Data Reveals Prioritized Therapeutic Candidates for Lung Squamous Cell Carcinoma.
abstract: Lung squamous cell carcinoma (LUSC) is the second most prevalent type of lung cancer worldwide. Despite its global health burden, the molecular mechanisms driving LUSC remain poorly characterized, posing considerable challenges for the development of targeted preventive therapies.
